Comment: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,EN,,0,0,0,,--------------------TEXT-EN--------------------
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.97,0:00:03.88,EN,,0,0,0,,What would you do if no one cared for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.40,0:00:07.19,EN,,0,0,0,,Imagine if you are honest about who you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.19,0:00:08.26,EN,,0,0,0,,you could be killed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.84,0:00:15.97,EN,,0,0,0,,That's always been the reality for many LGBT folks
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.97,0:00:17.73,EN,,0,0,0,,since the birth of America
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.73,0:00:20.08,EN,,0,0,0,,Many people lived in secret, fearful
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.08,0:00:22.25,EN,,0,0,0,,that someone would discover their truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.01,0:00:25.85,EN,,0,0,0,,That was a motivation for Walt Whitman to write poetry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.85,0:00:28.21,EN,,0,0,0,,that would beckon gay people to save places
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:30.32,EN,,0,0,0,,where they could build community.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.32,0:00:34.84,EN,,0,0,0,,Yet most LGBT people were still forced to live in isolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.24,0:00:37.90,EN,,0,0,0,,Then Karl-Maria Kertbeny gave us the term
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.90,0:00:40.35,EN,,0,0,0,,homosexual in the power to identify.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.67,0:00:43.71,EN,,0,0,0,,And writers like Alice Dunbar Nelson showed up
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.19,0:00:47.02,EN,,0,0,0,,As a biracial bisexual woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.02,0:00:49.65,EN,,0,0,0,,her courage in the face of prejudice allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.65,0:00:52.66,EN,,0,0,0,,more stories of LGBT people to be told.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.99,0:00:55.85,EN,,0,0,0,,Like that of the two spirits, you need Native American We'wha
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.85,0:00:58.07,EN,,0,0,0,,who impressed President Grover Cleveland.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.07,0:01:01.43,EN,,0,0,0,,But after her truth was fully known, she was villainized
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.97,0:01:07.80,EN,,0,0,0,,Overtime LGBT people congregated in safe spaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.80,0:01:12.84,EN,,0,0,0,,and we began to see more representation in art, books and theater
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.84,0:01:15.13,EN,,0,0,0,,America soon called women to fight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.13,0:01:18.86,EN,,0,0,0,,and a contingent of lesbians formed in the Women's Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.86,0:01:22.49,EN,,0,0,0,,which became a place where lesbian women could be themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.49,0:01:27.22,EN,,0,0,0,,After the war, many women refuse to go back to traditional gender norms
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.22,0:01:31.39,EN,,0,0,0,,All of this paved the way for the homophile area for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.39,0:01:36.58,EN,,0,0,0,,we saw people publicly demanding livable communities and LGBT equality.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.16,0:01:40.10,EN,,0,0,0,,Later, scientific studies prove that homosexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.10,0:01:41.85,EN,,0,0,0,,was not a psychiatric disorder
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.85,0:01:43.83,EN,,0,0,0,,that needed to be cured and put an end to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.83,0:01:47.46,EN,,0,0,0,,the practice of placing LGBT people in mental asylums.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.31,0:01:53.75,EN,,0,0,0,,Well, there was a growing restlessness among gender nonconformists,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.75,0:01:57.31,EN,,0,0,0,,one by one. LGBT folks rose up to defend themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.31,0:02:01.56,EN,,0,0,0,,rioting in places, like donut shops, cafeterias in bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:04.24,EN,,0,0,0,,Their courage sprung from Magnus Hirschfeld,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.24,0:02:07.97,EN,,0,0,0,,safe Haven for LGBT folks which inspired Henry Gerber
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.97,0:02:10.12,EN,,0,0,0,,to form the Society for Human Rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:13.31,EN,,0,0,0,,This motivated countless LGBT people to create,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.31,0:02:18.25,EN,,0,0,0,,change and establish more LGBT organizations across America.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.64,0:02:21.67,EN,,0,0,0,,By the time of Stonewall, it became impossible to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.67,0:02:23.97,EN,,0,0,0,,ignore the gay liberation movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.83,0:02:28.28,EN,,0,0,0,,Even the Rice leaders like Harvey Milk unapologetic Lee called for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.28,0:02:30.61,EN,,0,0,0,,each of us to live fearlessly in the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.01,0:02:35.29,EN,,0,0,0,,His murder and legacy inspired a new generation of civic activists,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.29,0:02:38.67,EN,,0,0,0,,fighting for the civil liberties of the LGBT people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.99,0:02:43.92,EN,,0,0,0,,In solidarity, LGBT people of all ages, races and genders,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.92,0:02:47.46,EN,,0,0,0,,and their allies demanded equality for their community
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.46,0:02:50.18,EN,,0,0,0,,at the first national gay rights march.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.02,0:02:58.89,EN,,0,0,0,,Then 1980s. How many calls gay cancer LGBT people
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.89,0:03:01.31,EN,,0,0,0,,with AIDS were denied healthcare.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.31,0:03:03.92,EN,,0,0,0,,Many politicians were apathetic, those afflicted
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.92,0:03:06.94,EN,,0,0,0,,hard to honest the will to survive against all odds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.94,0:03:10.59,EN,,0,0,0,,while many in America refused to acknowledge this epidemic,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:13.89,EN,,0,0,0,,people got angry, sparking a movement that encouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.89,0:03:17.31,EN,,0,0,0,,the community to act up when news revealed that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.31,0:03:20.02,EN,,0,0,0,,AIDS affected even those who are not homosexuals,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.02,0:03:22.64,EN,,0,0,0,,policies finally began to shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:26.52,EN,,0,0,0,,By then, an entire generation had already disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:29.87,EN,,0,0,0,,erasing many voices that carried our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.17,0:03:39.16,EN,,0,0,0,,Homophobia and transphobia led to the violent loss of more lives
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.16,0:03:43.45,EN,,0,0,0,,as gay activists lobbied for protections already offered to other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.97,0:03:48.74,EN,,0,0,0,,Then legislation criminalize discrimination against LGBT folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.10,EN,,0,0,0,,The military embrace gay Americans and did away with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.10,0:03:53.67,EN,,0,0,0,,'Don't ask, Don't tell'
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.27,0:03:58.57,EN,,0,0,0,,Gay couples gained the right to legally marry anywhere in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.91,0:04:02.29,EN,,0,0,0,,And now LGBT elders, like Marsha Wetzel are fighting and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.29,0:04:04.57,EN,,0,0,0,,winning legal battles for housing rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:07.53,EN,,0,0,0,,Underlining that everyone deserves freedom from harassment
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.53,0:04:10.64,EN,,0,0,0,,and discrimination, especially as we age.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:14.65,EN,,0,0,0,,Today, National Historic Landmarks recognize significant
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:17.50,EN,,0,0,0,,LGBT events as part of America's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.20,0:04:25.64,EN,,0,0,0,,When faced with death and injustice, LGBT people were forced
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.64,0:04:29.18,EN,,0,0,0,,to hide in the closet until the time was right to emerge as visible
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.18,0:04:31.13,EN,,0,0,0,,and vocal activists for equality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.40,0:04:36.33,EN,,0,0,0,,Even today, in the face of rising hate crimes under representation in denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:39.81,EN,,0,0,0,,LGBT people still struggle for acceptance and equality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.18,0:04:44.98,EN,,0,0,0,,Three and four LGBT older adults still worry about having enough
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.98,0:04:47.97,EN,,0,0,0,,support from family and friends as they age.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.59,0:04:52.85,EN,,0,0,0,,This fight continues and it's a fight where we all have a stake in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.77,0:04:58.12,EN,,0,0,0,,In the guiding words of AARP founders, Doctor Ethel Percy Andrus,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.12,0:05:00.61,EN,,0,0,0,,'What we do, we do for all'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.61,0:05:02.93,EN,,0,0,0,,our movement that started as a fight
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.93,0:05:06.18,EN,,0,0,0,,for survival has become a story of resilience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.67,0:05:11.73,EN,,0,0,0,,This is progress paved by heroes in the past, present and into the future
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:16.90,EN,,0,0,0,,Now more than ever, it's time for all of us to stand up, speak out,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.90,0:05:22.57,EN,,0,0,0,,and claimed care for ourselves for our LGBT community, and for our future.
Comment: 0,0:05:24.85,0:05:29.14,EN,,0,0,0,,A living history of the LGBT movement powered by AARP
Comment: 0,0:05:30.89,0:05:34.43,EN,,0,0,0,,Learn more at aarp.org/PRIDE
Comment: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,CN,,0,0,0,,--------------------TEXT-CN--------------------
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.97,0:00:03.88,CN,,0,0,0,,如果没人关心你，你会怎么办？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.40,0:00:07.19,CN,,0,0,0,,想象一下，如果你向他人表现真实的自己
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.19,0:00:08.26,CN,,0,0,0,,你可能会被杀
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.84,0:00:15.97,CN,,0,0,0,,这一直是自美国建国以来
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.97,0:00:17.73,CN,,0,0,0,,许多LGBT人群所面对的现实
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.73,0:00:20.08,CN,,0,0,0,,许多人一生活都活在阴影中
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.08,0:00:22.25,CN,,0,0,0,,害怕有人会发现真实的他们
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.01,0:00:25.85,CN,,0,0,0,,沃尔特·惠特曼的写作动机就在于此
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.85,0:00:28.21,CN,,0,0,0,,他的诗歌强有力地号召同性恋们
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.21,0:00:30.32,CN,,0,0,0,,联结属于他们自己的圈子
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.32,0:00:34.84,CN,,0,0,0,,然而大多数LGBT人士仍然被迫与世隔绝
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.24,0:00:37.90,CN,,0,0,0,,不久之后卡尔·玛利亚·克特本尼为我们提供了一个术语
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.90,0:00:40.35,CN,,0,0,0,,同性恋——赋予了他们确认自己身份的权利
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.67,0:00:43.71,CN,,0,0,0,,接着像爱丽丝·邓巴·纳尔逊这样的作家出现了
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.19,0:00:47.02,CN,,0,0,0,,作为一个双种族双性恋的女性
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.02,0:00:49.65,CN,,0,0,0,,她面对偏见的勇气帮助了
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.65,0:00:52.66,CN,,0,0,0,,更多的LGBT群体讲出他们的故事
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.99,0:00:55.85,CN,,0,0,0,,就像两种灵魂的共存，我们提到了威娃
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.85,0:00:58.07,CN,,0,0,0,,同美洲原住民一道散步给格罗夫·克利夫兰总统留下了深刻的印象
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.07,0:01:01.43,CN,,0,0,0,,但在她的秘密被公之于众后，她的名声受到了影响
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.97,0:01:07.80,CN,,0,0,0,,长久以来LGBT人士聚集在属于自己的安全空间
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.80,0:01:12.84,CN,,0,0,0,,但我们逐渐开始在艺术、书籍和戏剧中看到更多大胆的表达
Dialogue: 1,0:01:12.84,0:01:15.13,CN,,0,0,0,,很快美国呼吁妇女们为自己而战
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.13,0:01:18.86,CN,,0,0,0,,不同性向的妇女们共同组建了一支队伍
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.86,0:01:22.49,CN,,0,0,0,,这为女同性恋群体提供了容身之所
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.49,0:01:27.22,CN,,0,0,0,,战后，许多妇女拒绝回归传统的性别范式
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.22,0:01:31.39,CN,,0,0,0,,这一切首次为同性群体的发声铺平了道路
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.39,0:01:36.58,CN,,0,0,0,,我们看到人们公开要求建设宜居社区和LGBT平权
Dialogue: 1,0:01:37.16,0:01:40.10,CN,,0,0,0,,后来，科学研究证明同性恋
Dialogue: 1,0:01:40.10,0:01:41.85,CN,,0,0,0,,不是需要治愈的精神障碍
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.85,0:01:43.83,CN,,0,0,0,,并结束了把非异性恋群体
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.83,0:01:47.46,CN,,0,0,0,,安置在精神病院的做法
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.31,0:01:53.75,CN,,0,0,0,,性别不合规者们日渐不满于安于现状
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.75,0:01:57.31,CN,,0,0,0,,性少数群体们接连站起来为自己辩护
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.31,0:02:01.56,CN,,0,0,0,,在一些地方发生了暴乱，如甜甜圈店，酒吧的自助餐厅
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.97,0:02:04.24,CN,,0,0,0,,马格努斯·赫希菲尔德赋予了他们坚定的勇气
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.24,0:02:07.97,CN,,0,0,0,,性少数群体们的避风港启发了亨利·格伯
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.97,0:02:10.12,CN,,0,0,0,,最终成立了人权协会
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.48,0:02:13.31,CN,,0,0,0,,这激发了无数LGBT人士的创造力
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.31,0:02:18.25,CN,,0,0,0,,他们在美国各地改变和建立了更多的LGBT组织
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.64,0:02:21.67,CN,,0,0,0,,发展到石墙时期的时候，想要忽略同性恋解放运动
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.67,0:02:23.97,CN,,0,0,0,,变成了一件不可能的事情
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.83,0:02:28.28,CN,,0,0,0,,甚至像哈维·米尔克这样的种族领导人也开诚布公地呼吁
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.28,0:02:30.61,CN,,0,0,0,,我们每个人都应该无所畏惧地生活在自由和开放中
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.01,0:02:35.29,CN,,0,0,0,,他被谋杀的事件和他的遗志激励了新一代的公民活动家
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.29,0:02:38.67,CN,,0,0,0,,为LGBT人群的公民自由而战
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.99,0:02:43.92,CN,,0,0,0,,他们为所有年龄、种族、性别的LGBT者提供声援
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.92,0:02:47.46,CN,,0,0,0,,他们的盟友在第一次全国同性恋权利游行中
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.46,0:02:50.18,CN,,0,0,0,,要求他们的社区平等
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.02,0:02:58.89,CN,,0,0,0,,然后是二十世纪八十年代 众多患艾滋病同性恋者被归为癌症人群
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.89,0:03:01.31,CN,,0,0,0,,他们不能享受医保
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.31,0:03:03.92,CN,,0,0,0,,政治家们对此无动于衷
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.92,0:03:06.94,CN,,0,0,0,,饱受折磨的患者们不愿面对生活的重重困难
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.94,0:03:10.59,CN,,0,0,0,,与此同时在美国还有人不承认该种病症
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.59,0:03:13.89,CN,,0,0,0,,群众被激怒了 他们浩浩荡荡发起一场运动
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.89,0:03:17.31,CN,,0,0,0,,要求社会采取行动
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.31,0:03:20.02,CN,,0,0,0,,直到艾滋开始影响圈外人时
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.02,0:03:22.64,CN,,0,0,0,,政策才开始发生转变
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.64,0:03:26.52,CN,,0,0,0,,自那以后，整整一代这一群体的人也就彻底销声匿迹
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.52,0:03:29.87,CN,,0,0,0,,承载着历史回忆的声音也就这样被抹掉了
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.17,0:03:39.16,CN,,0,0,0,,对同性恋和变性人的恐慌引发众多暴力事件
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.16,0:03:43.45,CN,,0,0,0,,同性恋狂热分子也纷纷游说当局以求得更好的保护措施
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.97,0:03:48.74,CN,,0,0,0,,随即国家出台法案将歧视LGBT群体定为刑事犯罪
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.10,CN,,0,0,0,,军队欢迎LGBT群体成员参军入伍
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.10,0:03:53.67,CN,,0,0,0,,并废除过去的“不说，不问”政策
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.27,0:03:58.57,CN,,0,0,0,,同性恋夫妇取得在美国任何地方合法结婚的权利
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.91,0:04:02.29,CN,,0,0,0,,类似于玛莎·韦策尔这样的老者
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.29,0:04:04.57,CN,,0,0,0,,也在积极争取房屋的财产权
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.57,0:04:07.53,CN,,0,0,0,,并强调所有人都不应受到歧视和侵犯
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.53,0:04:10.64,CN,,0,0,0,,尤其是那些由年龄和性别所造成的
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.97,0:04:14.65,CN,,0,0,0,,当今 美国国家历史名胜清楚地认识到
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.65,0:04:17.50,CN,,0,0,0,,LGBT群体一事是美国历史的一部分
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.20,0:04:25.64,CN,,0,0,0,,当面对死亡和不公LGBT群体始终忍气吞声
Dialogue: 1,0:04:25.64,0:04:29.18,CN,,0,0,0,,直到时机成熟
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.18,0:04:31.13,CN,,0,0,0,,才有人为平等权利奔走呼号
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.40,0:04:36.33,CN,,0,0,0,,即便今天 为应对LGBT群体所受的日益严重的犯罪与厌恶 以及代表权利的缺失
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.33,0:04:39.81,CN,,0,0,0,,LGBT群体仍然坚持为获取普罗大众的认可和平等权作斗争
Dialogue: 1,0:04:40.18,0:04:44.98,CN,,0,0,0,,三四位群体中的老人担心随着年龄的增长
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.98,0:04:47.97,CN,,0,0,0,,他们是否还会得到充分的支持
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.59,0:04:52.85,CN,,0,0,0,,这场纷争还在继续 我们也都牵扯其中
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.77,0:04:58.12,CN,,0,0,0,,用美国AARP创始人埃塞尔·珀西·安德鲁斯博士的话来说
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.12,0:05:00.61,CN,,0,0,0,,“我们所做之事为的是所有人”
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.61,0:05:02.93,CN,,0,0,0,,这场运动以一场抗争开始
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.93,0:05:06.18,CN,,0,0,0,,生存已经成为一个关于韧性的故事
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.67,0:05:11.73,CN,,0,0,0,,这是英雄们在过去，现在和将来所铺就的道路
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.56,0:05:16.90,CN,,0,0,0,,如今比以往更是时候让我们所有人大声疾呼
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.90,0:05:22.57,CN,,0,0,0,,为我们LGBT群体呐喊 为了一个崭新的未来
